    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1943-12-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1943-12-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="870"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d870">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500C.115 28th Conference/29e: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in the United Kingdom</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Winant</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-12-16">December 16,
                            1943</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>7916. Please deliver immediately to Phelan, Acting Director of the International
                    Labor Organization, the following message “The United States Government wishes
                    to extend an invitation to the International Labor Organization to hold its next
                    Conference in the United States and it is suggested that the city of
                    Philadelphia would be a suitable place.”<note n="25" xml:id="d870fn25">A
                        memorandum of December 17, 1943, from the White House to the Secretary of
                        State, reported as follows: “The President has directed that the following
                        message be transmitted to Ambassador Winant in London: ‘Fully approve I.L.O.
                        meeting in U.S. Signed: Roosevelt.’” Ambassador Winant was so informed in
                        telegram 7949, December 17, 1 p.m. (500C.115 28th Conference/29b).</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
